NOTES

1. I spotted glitches 6-7 times throughout the movie.
The glitches existed in the DVD i used as source, not a problem
of the encode. The glitch only lasts for milliseconds.
Barely noticeable, you won't mind.
Here's a screenshot as an example:
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://imageshack.com/a/img839/1711/i6p2.png&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://imageshack.com/a/img839/1711/i6p2.png&lt;/a&gt;


2. The DVD i used was FS, there's no WS version of the movie but it was
released in theaters in 1.85 ascpect ratio back in the day.
I cropped the top and bottom of the frame and resized to WS resolution.
I trimmed the movie 88 times and each time i positioned the crop window
accordingly so everything is framed properly.
If the DVD is open matte then what you get here is original aspect ratio.
If the DVD is pan and scan then i cropped something which was already cropped.

Not sure about this, i read mixed opinions on the matter. All i can say is
it feels allright watching it, your choise.

Thanx to &quot;bob5695&quot; for his help on this.
